Clean_coup <- coup_data %>% 
  select( - c(unrealized, conspiracy, attempt, coup_id)) %>% 
  group_by(year) %>% 
  arrange(desc(year))
top_10_coups <- coup_data %>% 
  group_by(country) %>% 
  filter(event_type == "coup") %>% 
  select(country, event_type, realized) %>% 
  summarise(total_coup = sum(realized)) %>% 
  arrange(desc(total_coup)) %>% 
  slice(1:10) 

top_10_coups %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = fct_reorder(country, total_coup),
             y = total_coup)) +
  labs(title = "Top 10 Countries with the Most Successful Coups from 1945- 2019",
       subtitle = "South and Central American countries have had the most successful coups",
       caption = "Source: Cline Center Coup D’état Project Dataset",
       x = "Country",
       y = "Number of Successful Coups") +
  coord_flip() +
  theme_minimal() +
  geom_col(fill = "darkolivegreen4")

 realized_coup <- Clean_coup %>% 
                    group_by(country) %>% 
                    filter(event_type == "coup") %>% 
                    select(country, event_type, realized) %>% 
                    summarise(total_coup = sum(realized)) %>% 
                    arrange(desc(total_coup))
attempted_coups <-coup_data %>% 
                    group_by(country) %>% 
                    filter(attempt == 1) %>% 
                    select(country, attempt) %>% 
                    summarise(failed_attempts = sum(attempt)) %>% 
                    arrange(desc(failed_attempts)) %>% 
                    slice(1:10) 

attempted_coups %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = fct_reorder(country, failed_attempts),
             y = failed_attempts)) +
  labs(title = "Top 10 Countries with the Most Unsuccessful Coups from 1945- 2019",
       subtitle = "Coups fail all over the world",
       caption = "Source: Cline Center Coup D’état Project Dataset",
       x = "Country",
       y = "Number of Unsuccessful Coups") +
  coord_flip() +
  theme_minimal() +
  geom_col(fill = "darkolivegreen4")

grouped_coup <- Clean_coup %>% 
  group_by(country, event_type) %>% 
  summarise(Coups = n()) %>% 
  filter(event_type == "coup")
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'country'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
joined_data <-joinCountryData2Map(grouped_coup,
                                 joinCode = "NAME",
                                 nameJoinColumn = "country")
## 95 codes from your data successfully matched countries in the map

fit_event_type <-   stan_glm(formula = realized ~ event_type,
                         data = Clean_coup,
                         family = "binomial",
                         refresh = 0)

fit_2 <- stan_glm(formula = realized ~  popular + dissident + foreign + military + rebel + palace + auto,
                         data = Clean_coup,
                         family = "binomial",
                         refresh = 0)

print(fit_event_type)
## stan_glm

##  predictors:   3

##                      Median MAD_SD
## (Intercept)          -6.9    1.5

print(fit_2)

\(realized_{i} = \beta_0 + \beta_1 popular_{i} + \beta_2 dissident_{i} + \beta_3 foreign_{i} + \beta_4 military + \beta_5 rebel + \beta_6 palace_{i} + \beta_7 auto + \epsilon_{i}\)

newobsx <- tibble( popular = c(1,0), dissident =  1, foreign =  1,
                   military =  1, rebel = 1, palace =  1, auto =  1) %>% 
                   mutate(names = paste("popular", popular, sep = "_"))
                   
                  
                  

              
    
                 
#popular, dissident, foreign, military, rebel,palace, auto
                             

pe_x <- posterior_epred(fit_2, 
                 newdata = newobsx) %>% 
                 as_tibble() %>% 
                 set_names(newobsx$names) %>% 
                 pivot_longer(names_to = "coup_type",
                           values_to = "perc_realized",
                           cols = c("popular_1", "popular_0"))


pe_x %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = perc_realized, color = coup_type)) +
          geom_histogram(aes(y = after_stat(count/sum(count))),
                         alpha = 0.5, 
                         bins = 100,
                         fill = "darkorchid") +
        labs(x = "Estimated Sucess of Coup",
               y = "Probability") +
          scale_x_continuous(labels = scales::percent_format(accuracy = 1)) +
          scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::percent_format(accuracy = 1)) +
          theme_classic()

military = rep(c(1,0)), rebel = rep(c(1,0)), palace = rep(c(1,0)), auto = rep(c(1,0)) , names = paste(popular, dissident, foreign, military, rebel, palace, auto)

newobsz <- tibble( popular = 1, dissident =  1, foreign =  1,
                   military =  c(1,0), rebel = 1, palace =  1, auto =  1) %>% 
                   mutate(names = paste("military", popular, sep = "_"))
newobs <- (tibble(event_type = c("coup", "attempted", "conspiracy")))

pe_eventype <- posterior_epred(fit_event_type, 
                 newdata = newobs) %>% 
                 as_tibble() %>% 
                 rename(Attempted = `1`) %>% 
                 rename(Conspiracy = `2`) %>% 
                 rename(Coup = `3`) %>% 
                 pivot_longer(cols = c(Attempted, Conspiracy, Coup),
                              names_to =  "event_type",
                              values_to = "success") 

pe_eventype %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = success, fill = event_type)) +
    geom_dotplot() +
     labs(title = "Posterior for Coup Success",
         subtitle = "which is most likely to be successful?",
         caption = "From Coup Data Set",
         x = "Event Type",
         y = "Probability") + 
    scale_x_continuous(labels = scales::percent_format(accuracy = 1)) +
    scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::percent_format(accuracy = 1)) +
    theme_classic()
## `stat_bindot()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.
